
If you don't have  boost 1.49.0 already installed (or you have an other version of boost) run the set_boost_1_49_0.sh from a terminal. This shell script requires root privileges.
Copy and paste the following commands:

chmod +x set_boost_1_49_0.sh
sudo ./set_boost_1_49_0.sh

To use boost 1.49.0 copy and paste the foollowing lines in the CMakeLists.txt file, before find_package ( Boost 1.49 COMPONENTS ... REQUIRED).

set (Boost_NO_SYSTEM_PATHS ON)
set(BOOST_ROOT "/usr/boost_1_49_0")
set(BOOST_INCLUDEDIR "/usr/boost_1_49_0/include/")
set(BOOST_LIBRARYDIR "/usr/boost_1_49_0/lib/")
